The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                 LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 Max New York Life Insurance Company has launched Max New York Life Unit Builder, a flexible unit-linked insurance plan (Ulip), that offers up to 200 per cent guaranteed loyalty additions at maturity or death. The product offers three fund options  secure, balanced and dynamic. In the dynamic opportunities fund, the fund managers will shift the investment among equities, bonds and money market instruments, depending on the market conditions. Unit Builder offers the option of six switches and three redirections free every year.                            
	 ING Life has come out with a unit-linked plan, ING Prime Life, that offers return of initial allocation charges and helps customers save for their long-term needs. The plan offers return of up to 200 per cent of the initial allocation charges to customers. The product comes with benefits such as flexibility to extend the policy term and raising the sum assured every year.                             
	 Aviva has launched Aviva LifeShield Plus, a term insurance with the option of doubling the sum assured in the case of an accidental death. It also offers immediate payment of the sum assured in the case of critical illness or permanent total disability.                                                                                                                                
